01:13.974 --> 01:15.808
What time
are you coming over?

01:15.892 --> 01:19.278
Um, I thought
we were doing my place.

01:19.362 --> 01:21.597
No, because whenever
I'm at your place,

01:21.648 --> 01:24.700
all I can see is Tess
in a bed sheet.

01:24.767 --> 01:26.202
I'll be there at 9:00.

01:31.541 --> 01:33.442
Bran bars are forbidden
to first years.

01:33.493 --> 01:35.494
- Since when?
- Since two seconds ago.

01:35.579 --> 01:37.079
Order of the quartermaster,

01:37.130 --> 01:38.664
who is no longer
speaking with you.

01:38.748 --> 01:40.499
Rachel.
Hmm?

01:40.584 --> 01:41.967
Can you please instruct
the associate to your right

01:42.052 --> 01:43.952
to pass
the nondairy creamer?

01:44.004 --> 01:46.121
Louis, as I have been trying
to tell you in person,

01:46.173 --> 01:48.123
and in the note I left,

01:48.175 --> 01:50.893
and in your voice mail,

01:50.960 --> 01:52.428
I'm sorry.

01:52.479 --> 01:53.846
Do you know what
nondairy creamer is, Rachel?

01:53.930 --> 01:55.181
- Uh--
- It's a metaphor.

01:55.265 --> 01:56.899
The first sip, you think
it's real, you know?

01:56.966 --> 01:58.184
After all,
it wants you to believe

01:58.268 --> 01:59.935
that it's genuine
and it's good,

01:59.986 --> 02:02.137
and it's gonna deliver
on its promise.

02:02.189 --> 02:03.572
But then with time,

02:03.640 --> 02:05.680
you realize that it's
just a concoction of chemicals

02:05.742 --> 02:07.326
that's designed
to disguise the truth

02:07.410 --> 02:08.828
that it's actually
full of shit.

02:08.912 --> 02:10.196
Then why
are you drinking it?

02:10.280 --> 02:12.748
I'm lactose intolerant.

02:24.327 --> 02:25.261
I don't accept.

02:25.328 --> 02:26.629
Don't accept what?

02:26.680 --> 02:28.600
Whatever bullshit apology
you're here to give me.

02:28.632 --> 02:29.849
You gave me your word,

02:29.933 --> 02:31.413
and the second
you found out that Mike

02:31.434 --> 02:33.519
was actually gonna say yes,
you couldn't stand it.

02:33.603 --> 02:34.720
You sold me out.

02:34.804 --> 02:36.204
I'm not here
to give you an apology.

02:36.223 --> 02:39.024
I'm here to give you a case.

02:40.277 --> 02:41.810
Those are
the Hessington oil files.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.011
Yeah, you know what, Harvey?

02:43.063 --> 02:44.563
I don't want
your sloppy seconds.

02:44.648 --> 02:46.282
That takeover attempt's
gonna be dead in the water

02:46.349 --> 02:48.284
the second that Ava Hessington's
settlement goes public.

02:48.351 --> 02:50.319
Tony Gianopolous isn't
going to just sell his shares

02:50.370 --> 02:51.654
and go away.

02:51.705 --> 02:52.821
You're right.
You know what he's gonna do?

02:52.873 --> 02:54.206
He's gonna
leverage his position,

02:54.291 --> 02:55.958
and he's gonna get
as much greenmail as he can.

02:56.025 --> 02:57.660
Which is exactly
why I'm here.

02:57.711 --> 03:01.046
You're better suited
to beat him back than I am.

03:01.131 --> 03:02.464
You think I don't know that?

03:02.532 --> 03:06.335
I know you know it.
I want you to know I know it.

03:10.090 --> 03:12.975
Leave the box.

03:15.929 --> 03:18.514
Louis,
have you given any thought

03:18.565 --> 03:19.932
to a rebound associate?

03:20.016 --> 03:22.551
Harvey, come on, you know
I'm not that kind of guy.

03:22.602 --> 03:25.988
Come on, you have him
file a few interrogatories,

03:26.055 --> 03:28.023
maybe pick up your dry cleaning,
and then you cut him loose.

03:28.074 --> 03:29.525
With no strings attached?

03:29.576 --> 03:32.861
Better men than you
have done it.

03:32.913 --> 03:33.996
No.

03:34.063 --> 03:35.998
- Yep.
- Who, Baird?

03:36.065 --> 03:39.118
A week-long fling
I ended six days too late.

03:39.202 --> 03:40.536
Yeah, but Harvey,

03:40.587 --> 03:42.748
I don't just want a superficial
relationship, you know?

03:42.756 --> 03:44.506
I want a true mentee.

03:44.574 --> 03:46.342
Someone I can take
to the gun club or mudding

03:46.409 --> 03:47.793
or to the origami festival.

03:47.877 --> 03:51.096
Louis, you're gonna find
the right one.

03:54.351 --> 03:57.419
Origami festival?
Oh, my God.

04:09.232 --> 04:12.234
Well, this is a surprise.

04:12.285 --> 04:14.486
What?

04:14.571 --> 04:18.273
I just never thought I'd see
the great Harriet Specter

04:18.325 --> 04:20.409
making her own copies.

04:23.296 --> 04:26.215
Is that
what this thing does?

04:26.282 --> 04:28.050
You've never made a copy
in your life before, have you?

04:28.117 --> 04:30.502
Of course not,
I'm too busy being a badass

04:30.587 --> 04:31.754
and worrying about my hair.

04:31.805 --> 04:34.006
And your brilliant associate,
Michelle Ross,

04:34.090 --> 04:36.508
does all the hard work
for you anyway.

04:36.593 --> 04:38.894
You're goddamn right
she does.

04:38.961 --> 04:41.730
I'm really sorry

04:41.798 --> 04:44.400
for what I said
about having a life.

04:44.467 --> 04:47.102
I know.

04:47.153 --> 04:49.355
So we're good?

04:49.439 --> 04:50.439
We're good.

04:50.490 --> 04:52.441
And you and Mike,
you're good?

04:52.492 --> 04:53.942
Do you really think
that Harvey

04:53.994 --> 04:55.911
had an emotional epiphany
on his own?

04:55.978 --> 04:57.613
So you did forgive him?

04:57.664 --> 04:58.914
Yes.

04:58.981 --> 05:00.249
Well, he doesn't know that.

05:00.316 --> 05:03.168
Which is why I have
a triple-whip, double-fat,

05:03.253 --> 05:06.038
extra shot mocha latte
with caramel.

05:06.122 --> 05:07.489
Fair enough.

05:07.540 --> 05:09.425
But maybe it's time
you told him.

05:09.492 --> 05:11.260
So you decided
not to go back to London?

05:11.327 --> 05:13.178
Well, we have some
unfinished business to discuss,

05:13.263 --> 05:14.880
and I thought it best
to do it in person.

05:14.964 --> 05:16.131
The takeover attempt.

05:16.182 --> 05:18.050
Tony Gianopolous.

05:18.134 --> 05:20.686
Well, I've assigned it
to another attorney,

05:20.770 --> 05:24.523
but before you express
any concern, he's excellent.

05:24.607 --> 05:27.476
Well, not only
do I not have concerns,

05:27.527 --> 05:29.645
I'm glad
you've handed it off.

05:29.696 --> 05:31.480
And why is that?

05:31.531 --> 05:33.615
Because that way I know you'll
trust the man you're overseeing

05:33.683 --> 05:37.319
when you come and work for me.

05:37.370 --> 05:39.405
I have to say,
I'm flattered.

05:39.489 --> 05:40.689
I don't want you
to be flattered.

05:40.740 --> 05:42.708
I want you to say yes.

05:42.792 --> 05:45.210
As much success as I've had
with that line myself,

05:45.295 --> 05:48.029
I'm afraid
I'm not an oilman.

05:48.081 --> 05:49.498
The oil business
is about oil

05:49.549 --> 05:52.334
as much as you being
a lawyer is about the law.

05:52.385 --> 05:54.803
Every day is a knife fight
in a prison yard,

05:54.871 --> 05:58.223
and something tells me
you like a good knife fight.

05:58.308 --> 05:59.758
No rules in a knife fight.

05:59.843 --> 06:02.594
Harvey, I've just lost
my number two.

06:02.679 --> 06:05.347
I can't think of anyone better
to replace him.

06:05.398 --> 06:06.515
Ava

06:06.566 --> 06:08.183
I'm a woman
who gets what I want,

06:08.234 --> 06:10.235
and I am willing
to pay for it.

06:10.320 --> 06:12.721
Don't get me wrong,
I'm happy to whore myself out.

06:12.772 --> 06:15.274
I just prefer to have
more than one client.

06:15.358 --> 06:18.077
Harvey, what a coincidence.

06:18.161 --> 06:20.446
Cameron, I'm surprised
you can afford this place

06:20.530 --> 06:22.331
now that
you're unemployed again.

06:22.398 --> 06:24.950
Well, my temporary gig
isn't over just yet.

06:25.034 --> 06:27.903
You may think
you have them fooled, Cameron,

06:27.954 --> 06:30.071
but they'll figure you out
eventually.

06:30.123 --> 06:31.072
You didn't.

06:31.124 --> 06:32.374
What are you talking about?

06:32.425 --> 06:34.209
Ava Hessington,
you're under arrest.

06:34.260 --> 06:35.794
- What?
- On what charge?

06:35.879 --> 06:38.079
Conspiracy
to commit murder.

06:41.050 --> 06:43.251
This is bullshit, Cameron.
We had a deal.

06:43.303 --> 06:44.586
A deal where your client

06:44.637 --> 06:47.389
admitted to bribing
a foreign official.

06:47.440 --> 06:49.224
That Colonel
that she paid off?

06:49.275 --> 06:51.760
After that, six people
were killed by his troops.

06:51.811 --> 06:54.530
I give my driver a tip,
and then he runs over someone.

06:54.597 --> 06:56.365
Doesn't mean I had
anything to do with it.

06:56.432 --> 06:58.033
But if the person
he hit was me,

06:58.100 --> 06:59.568
sure would look like that.

06:59.619 --> 07:01.787
What the hell
are you talking about?

07:01.871 --> 07:03.622
All six people
did whatever they could

07:03.706 --> 07:05.824
to stop your client
from getting her pipeline.

07:05.909 --> 07:07.659
If that's all you got,
you don't have shit.

07:07.744 --> 07:09.378
She did this, Harvey.
You don't know her.

07:09.445 --> 07:10.946
Yeah, but I know you,

07:10.997 --> 07:11.997
and you don't give a damn

07:12.081 --> 07:14.049
about murder
in some foreign country.

07:14.116 --> 07:15.751
You took this case
to stick it to me.

07:15.802 --> 07:17.419
And I did.

07:17.470 --> 07:18.921
She admitted that was a bribe

07:18.972 --> 07:20.422
because she never thought we
would tie her to those deaths,

07:20.473 --> 07:21.473
and now I got her.

07:21.558 --> 07:22.679
And you didn't
see it coming,

07:22.759 --> 07:26.812
and there's nothing
you can do about it.

